The paper deals with face-based emotion recognition using deep learning techniques, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also addresses privacy concerns, which could be related to multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The proposed adversarial learning framework involves training a convolutional neural network (CNN), which is a machine learning technique, and thus could be related to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper discusses potential applications in well-being and healthcare, which could be related to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
